We invented RECON. to give a sustainable  alternative to the current value chain. Our goal is to save resources by offering  on-demand designs as well as creating high-quality denim  up-cycling pieces.


Currently, we are in the Fourth Industrial Revolution, the boundaries between physical ,digital and biological worlds are blurry. We want to embrace this technology to make a change. Change the world for the better. 

Every year globally 18,6 million tons of clothes land up In landfills. Lots of these clothes are not biodegradable and stay there for years. During the decomposing textiles generate greenhouse, methane gas and leach toxic chemicals and dyes into the groundwater and our soil. This is harmful to the planet.

We want to change these immense numbers of waste by using technology and creating a new subculture. We will use technology to create a unique on-demand shopping experience. We will teach our customers about upcycling and create a new subculture.  
 

Up cycling

We offer up cycled and on demand clothing pieces. We make the up cycled garments from donated denim. Our designers work hard to make an innovative design of the denim they get donated. We made the decision to work with denim because it's a durable material, and we want to sell quality pieces. 


On demand clothes

We use holograms to preview our garments in the stores, In the store garment can be pre ordered. Then the garment will be made only for you and shipped to you when ready. Our factory's are all located In Europe to reduce the co2 emissions. By this on demand clothing we try to reduce the number clothes that end up In landfills. 

Our goal of educating consumers

Through our transparent ideals through each of our clothing category, and of our value chain we have ensured to create a easy flow for you to learn to your best ability.

In store with using QR codes, Information will be shown like the pricing , spendings of the materials and construction, the workers, the shipping route, care label of the item (also found on the clothing). 

All of this will. also be in display with similar and more general information next to each item.

We also wants to create an emotional connection with the customers and allow the customers to create a more value-able and emotional connection with their garments. We decided to try to do this with a donation process for the up-cycling materials. If people donated clothing for up-cycling, the psychology of actually contributing or make something connects with people giving them a feeling of pride or reassures of its belonging or meaning to them.Not only. this but they will also contribute to our impact of trying to change the overconsumption of the current value chain, therefore they will be apart of a change in society.


 This cycled of feeling like they are doing something good, we hope it will attract customers and encourage them to continue to come back and repeat that cycle, which will only reenforce our hopeful outcome and mission to change the production of the worlds current chain.


Also to allure them even more, the new holographic displays of RECON. designs is a tailored and made to oder process. Therefore the customer will feel the senses of nobility and self assurances. We hope when wearing a garment of their specific need, they can feel comfortable and feel like they are one with their clothing
